1)    Openings in a vertical fire separation having a fire-resistance rating of not more than 1 h are allowed to be protected by wired glass assemblies, provided the wired glass is a)    not less than 6 mm thick;
b)    reinforced by a steel wire mesh in the form of diamonds, squares or hexagons having dimensions of
i)   approximately 25 mm across the flats, using wire of not less than 0.45 mm diameter, or
ii)   approximately 13 mm across the flats, using wire of not less than 0.40 mm diameter, the wire to be centrally embedded during manufacture and welded or intertwined at each intersection;
c)    set in fixed steel frames with metal not less than 1.35 mm thick and providing a glazing stop of not less than 20 mm on each side of the glass; and
d)    limited in area so that
